output.content: Agentic workflow editors represent a new paradigm in automation where AI agents can autonomously navigate, understand, and modify complex workflows based on natural language instructions. Unlike traditional workflow tools that require manual configuration and rigid rule-setting, these editors leverage large language models to interpret context, make intelligent decisions, and adapt processes dynamically. This approach dramatically reduces the technical expertise needed to create sophisticated automations while enabling more flexible, context-aware systems that can handle exceptions and edge cases with human-like reasoning.
